WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:20.195 --> 00:00:22.042
<i>My name is Max.</i>

3
00:00:22.810 --> 00:00:25.583
<i>My world is fire and blood.</i>

4
00:00:26.204 --> 00:00:29.380
<i>- Why are you hurting these people?
- It's the oil. stupid.</i>

5
00:00:29.417 --> 00:00:32.125
<i>- Oil wars.
- We are killing for gasoline.</i>

6
00:00:32.176 --> 00:00:34.192
<i>The world is actually
running out of water.</i>

7
00:00:34.193 --> 00:00:36.623
<i>Now there's the water wars.</i>

8
00:00:37.647 --> 00:00:40.232
<i>Once. I was a cop.</i>

9
00:00:40.247 --> 00:00:43.361
<i>A road warrior searching
for a righteous cause.</i>

10
00:00:43.362 --> 00:00:47.495
<i>- ...to the terminal freak-out point.
- Mankind has gone rogue. terrorizing itself.</i>

11
00:00:48.076 --> 00:00:49.805
<i>Thermonuclear skirmish.</i>

12
00:00:49.810 --> 00:00:51.219
<i>The earth is sour.</i>

13
00:00:51.220 --> 00:00:54.691
<i>- Our bones are poisoned.
- We have become half-life.</i>

14
00:00:55.681 --> 00:00:57.573
<i>As the world fell...</i>

15
00:00:57.761 --> 00:01:00.751
<i>...each of us. in our own way.
was broken.</i>

16
00:01:01.280 --> 00:01:04.273
<i>It was hard to know
who was more crazy:</i>

17
00:01:06.371 --> 00:01:09.770
<i>Me... or everyone else.</i>

18
00:01:12.409 --> 00:01:13.793
<i>Hello?</i>

19
00:01:16.136 --> 00:01:17.730
<i>Where are you?</i>

20
00:01:24.981 --> 00:01:26.401
<i>Where are you. Max?</i>

21
00:01:26.392 --> 00:01:28.620
<i>- Here they come again.
- Max Rockatansky.</i>

22
00:01:28.621 --> 00:01:31.989
<i>Worming their way
into the black matter of my brain.</i>

23
00:01:31.990 --> 00:01:34.257
<i>- Help us. Max.
- You promised to help us.</i>

24
00:01:38.281 --> 00:01:42.331
<i>I tell myself.
they cannot touch me.</i>

25
00:01:44.425 --> 00:01:46.136
<i>They are long dead.</i>

26
00:02:44.099 --> 00:02:48.912
<i>I am the one who runs
from both the living and the dead.</i>

27
00:02:49.544 --> 00:02:51.862
<i>Hunted by scavengers.</i>

28
00:02:52.570 --> 00:02:55.534
<i>Haunted by those
I could not protect.</i>

29
00:03:05.010 --> 00:03:07.440
<i>So I exist in this Wasteland.</i>

30
00:03:12.318 --> 00:03:16.399
<i>A man reduced to a single instinct:</i>

31
00:03:17.212 --> 00:03:18.582
<i>Survive.</i>

32
00:04:38.812 --> 00:04:40.985
Max? Is that you?

33
00:04:41.682 --> 00:04:42.774
Where were you?

34
00:04:45.136 --> 00:04:48.695
Help us. Where were you?
Where were you. Max?

35
00:05:05.085 --> 00:05:06.646
Where were you. Max?
Stop running.

36
00:05:08.468 --> 00:05:09.452
You let us die!

37
00:05:10.966 --> 00:05:12.373
You let us die!

38
00:05:12.635 --> 00:05:13.825
You let us die!

39
00:05:14.263 --> 00:05:15.703
You promised to help us!

40
00:05:15.783 --> 00:05:16.149
Why?

41
00:05:35.856 --> 00:05:37.656
Witness!

42
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:40.519
I got him.

43
00:06:30.162 --> 00:06:33.038
- We are War Boys!
- War Boys!

44
00:06:33.180 --> 00:06:36.381
- Kamakrazee War Boys!
- War Boys!

45
00:06:36.382 --> 00:06:39.949
Fucacima kamakrazee War Boys!

46
00:06:40.325 --> 00:06:42.201
Hooked on!

47
00:06:42.994 --> 00:06:46.901
- Today we're heading to Gas Town!
- Gas Town!

48
00:06:47.233 --> 00:06:49.478
<i>Today we're hauling Aqua Cola.</i>

49
00:06:49.952 --> 00:06:51.232
<i>Aqua Cola!</i>

50
00:06:51.700 --> 00:06:55.244
<i>- Today we're hauling produce!
- Produce!</i>

51
00:06:55.245 --> 00:06:57.478
<i>And today we're hauling
Mother's Milk!</i>

52
00:06:57.708 --> 00:06:59.179
Mother's Milk!

53
00:07:23.869 --> 00:07:28.447
Joe! Joe! Joe! Immortan Joe!

54
00:07:48.192 --> 00:07:51.695
Rev it up for the Immortan Joe!

55
00:07:59.542 --> 00:08:02.894
Once again. we send off my War Rig...

56
00:08:02.895 --> 00:08:08.954
...to bring back gasoline from Gas Town
and bullets from the Bullet Farm!

57
00:08:09.751 --> 00:08:15.340
Once again. I salute
my Imperator Furiosa!

58
00:08:15.625 --> 00:08:19.571
And I salute my half-life War Boys...

59
00:08:19.572 --> 00:08:24.815
...who will ride with me eternal
on the highways of Valhalla.

60
00:08:24.816 --> 00:08:27.200
V8! V8! V8! V8!

61
00:08:27.397 --> 00:08:30.104
I am your redeemer.

62
00:08:30.321 --> 00:08:37.505
It is by my hand you will rise
from the ashes of this world!

63
00:08:45.496 --> 00:08:47.899
It's coming. Get ready.

64
00:08:48.039 --> 00:08:52.003
Yes. Yes. Yes. It's coming.

65
00:09:48.604 --> 00:09:53.212
Do not. my friends.
become addicted to water.

66
00:09:53.342 --> 00:09:58.102
It will take hold of you
and you will resent its absence.

67
00:10:22.986 --> 00:10:24.381
Clear off!

68
00:10:26.077 --> 00:10:27.822
Get them all off!

69
00:10:28.616 --> 00:10:29.974
Clear off!

70
00:10:39.199 --> 00:10:41.881
Signal Gas Town.
Convoy's on its way.

71
00:11:09.500 --> 00:11:13.671
I got a War Boy running on empty.
Hook up that full-life.

72
00:11:17.258 --> 00:11:20.200
Hey! Careful.
That's a universal donor.

73
00:12:17.374 --> 00:12:19.326
Boss. we're not going to Gas Town?

74
00:12:21.978 --> 00:12:23.261
Bullet Farm?

75
00:12:25.850 --> 00:12:27.298
We're heading east.

76
00:12:29.185 --> 00:12:30.740
I'll pass it down the line.

77
00:12:32.053 --> 00:12:35.260
New orders!
Thunder up! Thunder up!

78
00:12:35.674 --> 00:12:37.424
This is not a supply run!

79
00:12:37.909 --> 00:12:40.848
- Go. Go.
- Ace. what's going on?

80
00:12:40.849 --> 00:12:41.800
We're heading east.

81
00:12:41.925 --> 00:12:44.176
- Why?
- I don't know. That's the order.

82
00:13:02.513 --> 00:13:05.907
- Moo.
- Hey. Pa. You know about this?

83
00:13:06.909 --> 00:13:09.344
Your produce ain't going to Gas Town.

84
00:13:19.143 --> 00:13:20.870
She's gone off-road...

85
00:13:21.374 --> 00:13:23.268
...into hostile territory.

86
00:13:25.375 --> 00:13:27.311
Why would she do that. dad?

87
00:13:29.078 --> 00:13:31.405
- Let me see. Let me see.
- Rictus. - I wanna see!

88
00:13:31.406 --> 00:13:34.500
Rictus. Go see what's agitating Dad.

89
00:14:02.678 --> 00:14:04.110
Splendid!

90
00:14:05.433 --> 00:14:06.883
Angharad!

91
00:14:16.569 --> 00:14:19.855
- Where are they?
- They are not your property!

92
00:14:19.856 --> 00:14:23.618
- Miss Giddy?
- You cannot own a human being!

93
00:14:23.811 --> 00:14:26.153
Sooner or later someone pushes back!

94
00:14:26.348 --> 00:14:28.478
Where is she taking them?

95
00:14:28.718 --> 00:14:30.935
She didn't take them.
They begged her to go!

96
00:14:32.943 --> 00:14:36.492
- Where is she taking them?
- A long way from you.

97
00:15:02.567 --> 00:15:03.889
Hey. what's happening?

98
00:15:06.179 --> 00:15:08.932
Slit! What's going on?

99
00:15:09.086 --> 00:15:11.271
- Slit!
- Treason. Betrayal.

100
00:15:11.272 --> 00:15:12.674
An Imperator gone rogue.

101
00:15:12.675 --> 00:15:14.225
An Imperator? Who?

102
00:15:14.451 --> 00:15:17.335
Furiosa! She took a lot of stuff
from Immortan Joe.

103
00:15:17.547 --> 00:15:20.723
- What stuff?
- Breeders! His prize breeders!

104
00:15:20.922 --> 00:15:23.295
He wants them back!
Not a hand laid on them.

105
00:15:30.398 --> 00:15:33.610
By my deeds I honor him.
V8.

106
00:15:37.249 --> 00:15:39.320
V8! V8! V8!

107
00:15:45.757 --> 00:15:47.521
- That's my wheel.
- I'm driving.

108
00:15:47.725 --> 00:15:49.802
- You're my lancer.
- I just promoted myself.

109
00:15:49.803 --> 00:15:52.395
No. Not today. Today is my day.

110
00:15:52.396 --> 00:15:55.210
Look at you. If you can't stand up.
you can't do war.

111
00:15:55.456 --> 00:15:59.188
- He's right. son.
- I'm not staying here dying soft.

112
00:15:59.398 --> 00:16:01.103
You're already a corpse.

113
00:16:01.277 --> 00:16:03.295
- I just need a top-up. More juice.
- No time!

114
00:16:04.152 --> 00:16:05.237
We take my Blood Bag.

115
00:16:05.404 --> 00:16:07.632
We take my Blood Bag
and strap him to the lancer's perch.

116
00:16:07.633 --> 00:16:09.875
It's got a muzzle on it.
It's a raging feral!

117
00:16:10.387 --> 00:16:12.579
That's right. High-octane
crazy blood filling me up.

118
00:16:17.855 --> 00:16:18.651
If I'm gonna die...

119
00:16:20.296 --> 00:16:22.074
...I'm gonna die historic
on the Fury Road.

120
00:16:28.658 --> 00:16:30.651
Yeah. Yeah.

121
00:16:30.804 --> 00:16:33.933
Organic. hitch up his Blood Bag.

122
00:16:34.362 --> 00:16:35.365
Right-o.

123
00:16:45.479 --> 00:16:49.481
How much more can they take from me?
They've got my blood. Now it's my car!

124
00:17:27.772 --> 00:17:29.335
Immortan!

125
00:17:30.085 --> 00:17:31.499
Immortan Joe!

126
00:17:34.466 --> 00:17:35.740
He looked at me!

127
00:17:36.515 --> 00:17:39.408
- He looked right at me!
- He looked at your Blood Bag!

128
00:17:39.603 --> 00:17:42.042
He turned his head.
He looked me in the eye.

129
00:17:42.219 --> 00:17:44.343
He was scanning the horizon.

130
00:17:44.803 --> 00:17:47.261
No. I am awaited.

131
00:17:47.896 --> 00:17:49.926
I am awaited in Valhalla!

132
00:17:52.578 --> 00:17:54.426
Confucamus!

133
00:17:56.953 --> 00:17:57.942
Immortan!

134
00:18:20.269 --> 00:18:23.137
- Hey! Heads up!
- Heads up!

135
00:18:28.136 --> 00:18:29.019
Boss!

136
00:18:30.228 --> 00:18:33.250
We got vehicles from the Citadel.
They're firing flares.

137
00:18:33.251 --> 00:18:36.252
They want reinforcements
from Gas Town and the Bullet Farm.

138
00:18:36.458 --> 00:18:38.600
What is this?
Backup? Decoy?

139
00:18:40.224 --> 00:18:41.455
It's a detour.

140
00:19:13.907 --> 00:19:14.764
Eyes right!

141
00:19:18.180 --> 00:19:19.195
Buzzards!

142
00:19:19.509 --> 00:19:23.625
- Buzzards right! Eyes on! Eyes on!
- Buzzards right! Eyes on!

143
00:19:26.496 --> 00:19:29.399
Should we turn it around
and run them into our backup?

144
00:19:31.232 --> 00:19:32.789
No! We're good!

145
00:19:33.763 --> 00:19:34.986
We fang it!

146
00:19:38.409 --> 00:19:40.530
Thunder up! Here we go!

147
00:19:43.604 --> 00:19:45.140
Prepare the gunners!

148
00:20:14.525 --> 00:20:15.760
Morsov!

149
00:20:32.937 --> 00:20:33.561
War!

150
00:20:42.429 --> 00:20:43.411
Ready!

151
00:21:27.778 --> 00:21:30.308
She's ours. Slit!
She's ours.

152
00:21:30.374 --> 00:21:32.791
First. we get the Buzzards off her back!

153
00:21:38.906 --> 00:21:39.802
Form up!

154
00:21:44.113 --> 00:21:45.116
That's my head!

155
00:22:20.491 --> 00:22:22.483
Get up! You can do it!

156
00:22:27.744 --> 00:22:28.676
Morsov!

157
00:22:30.253 --> 00:22:32.397
- Morsov!
- No!

158
00:22:32.687 --> 00:22:35.300
- Witness me!
- Witness!

159
00:22:46.864 --> 00:22:48.268
- Witness!
- Witness!

160
00:22:50.014 --> 00:22:53.929
- Mediocre. Morsov!
- Mediocre!

161
00:23:27.910 --> 00:23:28.758
Back me in!

162
00:23:33.113 --> 00:23:34.070
They're coming!

163
00:23:51.996 --> 00:23:55.040
- We can't breathe down there!
- Stay out of sight!

164
00:23:56.243 --> 00:23:56.860
Now!

165
00:24:09.425 --> 00:24:10.360
Go back!

166
00:24:11.818 --> 00:24:12.470
Where's he going?

167
00:24:12.860 --> 00:24:14.415
Hydraulics! Hydraulics!

168
00:24:42.969 --> 00:24:44.903
Now we bring home the booty.

169
00:25:11.665 --> 00:25:13.538
She thinks she can lose us. Dad.

170
00:25:13.963 --> 00:25:15.740
She thinks we're stupid.

171
00:25:16.089 --> 00:25:18.168
She thinks she can lose us in there!

172
00:25:37.193 --> 00:25:39.958
Fang it! Fang it!

173
00:25:46.238 --> 00:25:47.058
Why can't you stop?

174
00:25:48.546 --> 00:25:51.047
Crew! Out of the way!
Out of the way!

175
00:25:51.240 --> 00:25:52.291
What have you done?

176
00:25:52.853 --> 00:25:53.834
What have you done?

177
00:26:16.090 --> 00:26:18.052
We need counterweight.
Get the Blood Bag down the back.

178
00:26:29.192 --> 00:26:31.702
Hunt them down! Hunt them down!

179
00:26:57.460 --> 00:27:00.930
Hey. head! Say bye-bye to the neck!
Decapito!

180
00:27:01.139 --> 00:27:01.806
We're going in. Slit!

181
00:28:04.755 --> 00:28:07.200
Come on! We've almost got her!

182
00:28:15.391 --> 00:28:18.367
Come on! Hold it steady!

183
00:28:45.837 --> 00:28:48.219
Oh. what a day!
What a lovely day!

184
00:29:08.025 --> 00:29:09.170
I'm the man...

185
00:29:09.882 --> 00:29:11.002
...who grabs the sun...

186
00:29:13.920 --> 00:29:15.636
...riding to Valhalla!

187
00:29:18.500 --> 00:29:20.075
Witness me. Blood Bag!

188
00:29:24.488 --> 00:29:25.736
Witness!

189
00:29:49.854 --> 00:29:51.969
I live. I die. I live again!

190
00:33:35.070 --> 00:33:36.349
We're not going back.

191
00:34:05.460 --> 00:34:06.579
Water.

192
00:35:02.333 --> 00:35:02.796
You.

193
00:35:18.291 --> 00:35:22.987
Angharad. is that just the wind
or is that a furious vexation?

194
00:36:52.846 --> 00:36:53.763
I got it!

195
00:37:35.470 --> 00:37:38.412
Glory me. Blood Bag!
We snagged her alive.

196
00:37:38.657 --> 00:37:41.105
He's gonna shred her.
Shred her!

197
00:37:41.266 --> 00:37:44.084
Bolt cutters. Chain.

198
00:37:51.149 --> 00:37:52.198
Oh. look at them.

199
00:37:52.846 --> 00:37:55.313
So shiny. So chrome.

200
00:37:55.767 --> 00:37:56.903
He's gonna be so grateful.

201
00:37:57.959 --> 00:37:59.379
We could ask for anything.

202
00:38:00.409 --> 00:38:01.982
I wanna drive the War Rig.

203
00:38:03.436 --> 00:38:05.436
- What are you gonna ask for?
- That's my jacket.

204
00:38:06.335 --> 00:38:07.337
Heh. heh. Sure.

205
00:38:08.392 --> 00:38:11.253
- You can ask for more than a jacket.
- We're going to the Green Place.

206
00:38:11.453 --> 00:38:12.248
Wait. it's you and me. Ugh!

207
00:38:26.821 --> 00:38:29.338
We're going to the Green Place
of Many Mothers.

208
00:38:47.856 --> 00:38:51.079
- How does it feel?
- It hurts.

209
00:38:51.150 --> 00:38:53.052
Out here. everything hurts.

210
00:38:54.971 --> 00:38:56.317
You wanna get through this?

211
00:39:00.226 --> 00:39:01.143
Do as I say.

212
00:39:06.538 --> 00:39:08.218
Now pick up what you can and run.

213
00:39:50.943 --> 00:39:52.340
Kill switches.

214
00:39:54.022 --> 00:39:55.546
I set the sequence myself.

215
00:39:55.947 --> 00:39:57.725
This Rig goes nowhere without me.

216
00:40:01.654 --> 00:40:02.952
You can get in.

217
00:40:04.344 --> 00:40:05.560
Not without them.

218
00:40:14.148 --> 00:40:15.321
So we wait.

219
00:40:24.212 --> 00:40:26.619
You're relying on the gratitude
of a very bad man.

220
00:40:26.972 --> 00:40:29.820
You've damaged one of his Wives.
How grateful do you think he's gonna be?

221
00:40:37.012 --> 00:40:40.080
You're sitting on 2000 horsepower
of nitro-boosted war machine.

222
00:40:41.095 --> 00:40:43.610
I'd say you got
about a five-minute head start.

223
00:40:51.858 --> 00:40:53.220
You want that thing off your face?

224
00:41:06.161 --> 00:41:07.051
Let's go.

225
00:41:51.632 --> 00:41:55.161
Of all the legs you had to shoot.
that one was attached to his favorite.

226
00:42:16.042 --> 00:42:16.837
Smeg!

227
00:42:37.389 --> 00:42:40.246
- You don't have to do it just because he
tells you. - What choice does she have?

228
00:42:40.247 --> 00:42:41.777
He's not gonna hurt us.
He needs us.

229
00:42:41.778 --> 00:42:44.379
- Why? - To bargain.
- Oh. he'll hurt us alright.

230
00:42:44.380 --> 00:42:46.718
- Think he's coming to the Green Place?
- Never!

231
00:42:46.849 --> 00:42:49.029
He's a crazy smeg who eats schlanger!

232
00:43:16.144 --> 00:43:18.100
- Nah. stay out of there.
- Behind you.

233
00:43:23.097 --> 00:43:24.408
The Gas Town Boys.

234
00:43:26.350 --> 00:43:28.035
Don't damage the goods.

235
00:43:34.741 --> 00:43:35.936
What do you see?

236
00:43:38.385 --> 00:43:39.898
Big Rigs...

237
00:43:41.522 --> 00:43:42.901
...Polecats...

238
00:43:43.626 --> 00:43:44.766
...Flamers...

239
00:43:46.600 --> 00:43:49.018
...and there's the People Eater himself.

240
00:43:50.215 --> 00:43:52.166
Coming to count the cost.

241
00:44:08.470 --> 00:44:12.052
We're dragging something out back.
I think it's the fuel pod.

242
00:44:13.079 --> 00:44:13.811
No. no.

243
00:44:15.525 --> 00:44:16.669
I'll go.

244
00:45:40.456 --> 00:45:41.708
Filth! You traitored him!

245
00:45:46.640 --> 00:45:49.470
- No unnecessary killing!
- This War Boy wants me dead!

246
00:45:49.471 --> 00:45:52.334
- We agreed!
- He's kamakrazee!

247
00:45:53.041 --> 00:45:54.916
He's just a kid
at the end of his half-life!

248
00:45:55.246 --> 00:45:57.251
No! I live. I die. I live again!

249
00:45:57.956 --> 00:45:59.674
- Hold him!
- Tie him up!

250
00:45:59.804 --> 00:46:02.146
- Throw him out!
- Chuck him out!

251
00:46:03.456 --> 00:46:04.943
You got more friends.

252
00:46:07.405 --> 00:46:10.873
Bullet Farmer.
They're coming from the Bullet Farm.

253
00:46:12.335 --> 00:46:14.081
It's over. You can't defy him.

254
00:46:14.804 --> 00:46:15.673
Just watch us. mate!

255
00:46:15.674 --> 00:46:18.856
- He is the one who grabbed the sun.
- Look how slick he's fooled you. War Boy.

256
00:46:19.000 --> 00:46:20.483
He's a lying old man.

257
00:46:20.744 --> 00:46:22.075
By his hand we'll be lifted up!

258
00:46:22.076 --> 00:46:24.449
That's why we have
his logo seared on our backs!

259
00:46:24.671 --> 00:46:26.416
"Breeding Stock"!
"Battle Fodder"!

260
00:46:26.545 --> 00:46:27.571
No. I am awaited!

261
00:46:27.765 --> 00:46:29.703
You're an old man's "Battle Fodder"!

262
00:46:29.704 --> 00:46:31.523
Killing everyone and everything!

263
00:46:31.790 --> 00:46:33.735
- We're not to blame!
- Then who killed the world?

264
00:47:02.044 --> 00:47:03.890
I made a deal up ahead. Safe passage.

265
00:47:04.738 --> 00:47:06.433
I don't know if it's still any good.

266
00:47:07.440 --> 00:47:10.118
Get back in the hold!
Keep the hatch open.

267
00:47:17.533 --> 00:47:18.360
I need you here.

268
00:47:20.788 --> 00:47:22.203
You may have to drive the Rig.

269
00:47:27.990 --> 00:47:28.959
You.

270
00:47:29.995 --> 00:47:30.847
You stay.

271
00:47:32.081 --> 00:47:33.151
You stay there.

272
00:47:36.862 --> 00:47:38.840
Whatever you do. you can't be seen.

273
00:47:39.493 --> 00:47:42.667
I'm supposed to be alone.
That was the deal.

274
00:47:49.576 --> 00:47:50.614
Down here.

275
00:48:13.707 --> 00:48:14.659
What's your name?

276
00:48:16.899 --> 00:48:18.418
What do I call you?

277
00:48:19.234 --> 00:48:20.140
Does it matter?

278
00:48:22.705 --> 00:48:23.711
Fine.

279
00:48:24.362 --> 00:48:27.594
When I yell "fool". you drive
out of here as fast as you can.

280
00:48:29.723 --> 00:48:31.128
This is the sequence:

281
00:48:31.770 --> 00:48:34.766
One. One. two. One.

282
00:48:35.400 --> 00:48:37.753
Red. Black. Go.

283
00:48:38.665 --> 00:48:39.973
You have it?

284
00:50:05.294 --> 00:50:06.780
It's all here!

285
00:50:07.988 --> 00:50:10.875
3.000 gallons of gasoline.
just like you asked!

286
00:50:15.023 --> 00:50:16.625
I'm gonna unhitch the pod.

287
00:50:18.750 --> 00:50:20.332
You drop the rocks.

288
00:50:28.802 --> 00:50:33.386
You said:
"A few vehicles in pursuit. Maybe."

289
00:50:33.903 --> 00:50:36.187
We count three War Parties!

290
00:50:37.108 --> 00:50:38.962
Yeah. well. I got unlucky.

291
00:50:39.449 --> 00:50:40.630
Let's do this!

292
00:51:07.626 --> 00:51:08.425
Fool!

293
00:51:49.389 --> 00:51:50.943
That's our fuel!

294
00:52:05.503 --> 00:52:07.462
Make way for the Ripsaw!

295
00:52:22.744 --> 00:52:26.755
Once I'm over. clear the rocks
and bring everyone through.

296
00:52:26.756 --> 00:52:29.738
Immortan!
Immortan Joe!

297
00:52:30.001 --> 00:52:33.102
I got a War Boy!
Says he was on the War Rig.

298
00:52:35.840 --> 00:52:37.540
You! Climb aboard!

299
00:52:42.068 --> 00:52:45.572
I got his boot!
I got the Blood Bag's boot!

300
00:52:46.120 --> 00:52:49.296
Take me! I got his boot!

301
00:52:51.365 --> 00:52:53.808
All this for a family squabble.

302
00:52:54.651 --> 00:52:56.494
Healthy babies.

303
00:55:04.341 --> 00:55:05.535
Reload the clip.

304
00:55:06.740 --> 00:55:07.718
I can't.

305
00:55:14.543 --> 00:55:15.027
Gun!

306
00:55:16.923 --> 00:55:18.433
- Gimme the gun!
- Not loaded yet!

307
00:55:18.649 --> 00:55:20.541
- Now!
- We had a deal!

308
00:56:09.390 --> 00:56:10.588
Rictus!

309
00:56:11.140 --> 00:56:13.570
The Wives!
No more flames.

310
00:56:20.543 --> 00:56:21.689
Splendid!

311
00:56:22.445 --> 00:56:23.317
Splendid!

312
00:56:23.734 --> 00:56:27.026
That's my child!
My property!

313
00:56:29.239 --> 00:56:29.901
Immorta--

314
00:56:39.726 --> 00:56:43.279
Immortan. If I get on the Rig.
there's a way inside.

315
00:56:43.769 --> 00:56:45.804
- What is your name?
- It's Nux.

316
00:56:46.310 --> 00:56:48.428
I'll pike her in the spine.
Keep her breathing for you.

317
00:56:48.867 --> 00:56:49.696
No.

318
00:56:50.236 --> 00:56:51.812
Put a bullet in her skull...

319
00:56:51.860 --> 00:56:54.535
...stop the Rig.
return my treasures to me...

320
00:56:55.086 --> 00:57:00.468
...and I. myself. will carry you
to the Gates of Valhalla.

321
00:57:01.109 --> 00:57:02.104
Am I awaited?

322
00:57:03.295 --> 00:57:07.081
You will ride eternal.
shiny and chrome.

323
00:57:08.607 --> 00:57:12.053
Rictus! Help him aboard!

324
00:57:13.699 --> 00:57:14.856
Ready?

325
00:57:15.460 --> 00:57:16.533
Here we go!

326
00:57:28.720 --> 00:57:30.347
Mediocre!

327
00:58:00.303 --> 00:58:01.021
Schlanger!

328
00:58:21.978 --> 00:58:22.743
Look out!

329
00:58:26.616 --> 00:58:29.109
Angharad! Get out!

330
00:58:50.068 --> 00:58:51.921
- No!
- Angharad!

331
00:59:06.840 --> 00:59:08.983
Stop! Turn the Rig around!

332
00:59:10.088 --> 00:59:11.400
Go back for her!

333
00:59:12.895 --> 00:59:13.850
No.

334
00:59:13.961 --> 00:59:16.684
- Tell him to turn the Rig around!
- Did you see it?

335
00:59:17.352 --> 00:59:20.890
- She went under the wheels.
- Did you see it?

336
00:59:22.555 --> 00:59:24.143
She went under the wheels.

337
00:59:25.562 --> 00:59:27.498
- We keep moving.
- No!

338
00:59:27.638 --> 00:59:30.333
- We keep moving!
- He doesn't know what he's talking about!

339
00:59:31.089 --> 00:59:33.094
Whatever happens.
we're going to the Green Place.

340
00:59:33.095 --> 00:59:35.598
The stupid Green Place.
We don't even know where to find it!

341
00:59:48.396 --> 00:59:50.581
- You all right?
- On! On!

342
01:00:28.888 --> 01:00:29.891
Cheedo!

343
01:00:30.568 --> 01:00:32.977
- Cheedo. don't be stupid.
- Stop!

344
01:00:33.254 --> 01:00:36.291
- He'll forgive us. I know he will.
- There is no going back!

345
01:00:36.486 --> 01:00:39.723
- We were his treasures!
- Cheedo! - We were protected!

346
01:00:39.724 --> 01:00:43.201
- He gave us the high life! What's wrong
with that? - We are not things.

347
01:00:44.416 --> 01:00:45.210
No!

348
01:00:46.683 --> 01:00:49.645
- Cheedo. we are not things!
- We are not things.

349
01:00:49.646 --> 01:00:51.102
I don't want to hear that again!

350
01:00:51.103 --> 01:00:53.877
- They were her words!
- And now she's dead!

351
01:00:55.122 --> 01:00:57.883
Wring your hands and tear your hair
but you're not going back.

352
01:00:58.420 --> 01:01:01.585
- You're not going back to him.
- Angharad!

353
01:01:01.607 --> 01:01:03.247
Come on! Come on!

354
01:01:20.878 --> 01:01:22.251
So. um. ahem...

355
01:01:23.505 --> 01:01:25.036
...where is this...

356
01:01:26.512 --> 01:01:28.345
...Green Place?

357
01:01:29.417 --> 01:01:31.398
It's a long night's run. heading east.

358
01:01:33.913 --> 01:01:37.720
We need inventory. I want you
to match every gun with its bullets.

359
01:01:41.798 --> 01:01:45.269
- I'm gonna go and do some repairs.
- We need someone down the back.

360
01:01:45.394 --> 01:01:46.993
- I'll go.
- No.

361
01:01:47.231 --> 01:01:48.887
I want you to stay together.

362
01:01:49.598 --> 01:01:50.816
I can do it.

363
01:02:24.019 --> 01:02:25.141
What are you doing here?

364
01:02:26.520 --> 01:02:29.797
He saw it.
He saw it all.

365
01:02:31.209 --> 01:02:33.698
My own Blood Bag
driving the Rig that killed her.

366
01:02:41.717 --> 01:02:42.678
Stop doing that.

367
01:02:46.345 --> 01:02:47.288
Stop.

368
01:02:57.940 --> 01:03:00.269
Three times the gates were open to me.

369
01:03:00.753 --> 01:03:04.113
- What gates?
- I was awaited in Valhalla.

370
01:03:04.366 --> 01:03:06.024
They were calling my name.

371
01:03:06.732 --> 01:03:10.434
I should be walking with the Immortan.
Feasting with the heroes of all time.

372
01:03:13.982 --> 01:03:17.104
I'd say it was
your manifest destiny not to.

373
01:03:18.792 --> 01:03:21.408
I thought I was being spared
for something great.

374
01:03:21.624 --> 01:03:25.266
I got to drive a pursuit vehicle.

375
01:03:25.931 --> 01:03:28.984
For a while even Larry and Barry
stopped chewing on my windpipe.

376
01:03:29.521 --> 01:03:31.091
Who are Larry and Barry?

377
01:03:32.008 --> 01:03:33.226
My mates.

378
01:03:33.807 --> 01:03:35.270
Larry and Barry.

379
01:03:37.697 --> 01:03:39.766
If they don't get me.
then the Night Fevers will.

380
01:04:04.380 --> 01:04:08.056
Well. we've only got four for Big Boy here.
so he's all but useless.

381
01:04:09.526 --> 01:04:15.058
But... we can squirt off this little pinky
a raunchy 29 times.

382
01:04:17.318 --> 01:04:19.368
Angharad used to call them Antiseed.

383
01:04:20.422 --> 01:04:22.707
Plant one and watch something die.

384
01:05:35.533 --> 01:05:36.973
Watch out!

385
01:05:38.351 --> 01:05:39.929
Hold on. mate.

386
01:05:57.911 --> 01:06:01.021
We are down
30.000 units of gasoline...

387
01:06:01.261 --> 01:06:05.125
...19 canisters of nitro.
12 assault bikes...

388
01:06:05.126 --> 01:06:06.838
...7 pursuit vehicles.

389
01:06:06.843 --> 01:06:09.358
The deficit mounts.
And now. sir...

390
01:06:09.693 --> 01:06:12.538
...you have us stuck in a quagmire.

391
01:06:13.187 --> 01:06:14.232
Hey. Joe!

392
01:06:15.196 --> 01:06:16.165
Boss!

393
01:06:18.359 --> 01:06:20.514
Your girly's breathing her last!

394
01:06:21.125 --> 01:06:22.994
What about the child?

395
01:06:32.225 --> 01:06:35.070
- Are you coming. brother?
- Wait!

396
01:06:36.284 --> 01:06:39.286
- It's gone awful quiet in there...
- Get it out.

397
01:06:39.521 --> 01:06:40.769
Get it out!

398
01:06:43.694 --> 01:06:45.773
Come on!
I've been called to the torture!

399
01:06:46.859 --> 01:06:48.456
Patience!

400
01:06:49.457 --> 01:06:51.789
Oh. you stay here
with your grief. Daddy.

401
01:06:52.146 --> 01:06:56.088
- I'll fetch them for you.
- Be careful! Protect the assets!

402
01:06:57.847 --> 01:07:00.163
Just one angry shot...

403
01:07:00.760 --> 01:07:03.470
...for Furiosa.
Hut!

404
01:07:11.180 --> 01:07:12.920
Crying shame. Heh.

405
01:07:16.233 --> 01:07:20.118
Another month... could have been
your viable human!

406
01:07:20.129 --> 01:07:23.181
- Was it a male?
- Your A-1 Alpha prime.

407
01:07:26.431 --> 01:07:27.655
Hey. Rictus!

408
01:07:29.016 --> 01:07:30.786
You lost a baby brother!

409
01:07:33.134 --> 01:07:35.054
Perfect in every way.

410
01:07:37.814 --> 01:07:41.792
I had a baby brother!
I had a little baby brother!

411
01:07:41.997 --> 01:07:43.635
And he was perfect!

412
01:07:43.912 --> 01:07:45.831
Perfect in every way!

413
01:08:16.644 --> 01:08:17.591
Come on.

414
01:08:27.123 --> 01:08:30.239
- Wouldn't wanna shoot the Wives. sir.
- Just probing.

415
01:08:41.639 --> 01:08:44.139
- He wants to help!
- Who?

416
01:08:44.477 --> 01:08:45.764
The War Boy!

417
01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:48.894
- Where did he come from?
- I thought we threw him off the Rig!

418
01:08:53.619 --> 01:08:55.596
There's high ground
just beyond that thing.

419
01:08:55.719 --> 01:08:58.588
- He means the tree.
- Yeah. Tree!

420
01:09:00.185 --> 01:09:02.788
- Leave him to me.
- Say. anyone notice that bright light?

421
01:09:02.860 --> 01:09:04.445
Encroaching gunfire?

422
01:09:05.292 --> 01:09:07.374
- Get out.
- I can do this. I know this machine.

423
01:09:07.497 --> 01:09:08.976
He does. He's a Revhead.

424
01:09:14.839 --> 01:09:16.422
You've got two left!

425
01:09:22.151 --> 01:09:23.166
On him.

426
01:09:40.922 --> 01:09:42.269
Don't breathe.

427
01:09:48.859 --> 01:09:49.790
War Boy!

428
01:09:50.093 --> 01:09:52.452
I'm gonna use the winch
around the tree thing!

429
01:09:53.628 --> 01:09:54.692
Take this.

430
01:09:54.990 --> 01:09:56.456
Let's get the engine plates.

431
01:09:58.006 --> 01:09:58.956
You drive the Rig!

432
01:09:59.242 --> 01:10:00.980
- Hold up a flare!
- I am holding a flare!

433
01:10:01.789 --> 01:10:04.263
- Closer!
- It's right in front of your eyes!

434
01:10:16.552 --> 01:10:18.393
Hut! Hut!

435
01:10:24.631 --> 01:10:25.665
Blood Bag!

436
01:10:32.270 --> 01:10:34.612
I am the scales of justice!

437
01:10:34.955 --> 01:10:37.455
Conductor of the choir of death!

438
01:10:38.647 --> 01:10:40.332
<i>Sing. Brother Heckler!</i>

439
01:10:42.019 --> 01:10:43.520
Sing. Brother Koch!

440
01:10:46.572 --> 01:10:50.080
Sing. brothers. sing! Sing!

441
01:10:51.312 --> 01:10:52.974
Don't they know
they're shooting at us?

442
01:11:07.312 --> 01:11:08.487
Gun fever!

443
01:12:18.948 --> 01:12:20.986
I never thought I'd do something
as shiny as that.

444
01:12:21.658 --> 01:12:22.970
How are the engines?

445
01:12:23.818 --> 01:12:25.129
Very hot and real thirsty.

446
01:12:31.466 --> 01:12:34.309
You need to take the War Rig
half a klick down the track.

447
01:12:35.288 --> 01:12:37.868
What if you're not back by the time
the engines have cooled?

448
01:12:40.462 --> 01:12:41.738
Well. you keep moving.

449
01:12:51.388 --> 01:12:53.288
What do you suppose he's gonna do?

450
01:12:54.458 --> 01:12:56.277
Retaliate first.

451
01:12:59.425 --> 01:13:00.554
Let's go!

452
01:14:20.444 --> 01:14:21.711
Are you hurt?

453
01:14:23.340 --> 01:14:24.300
You're bleeding.

454
01:14:25.174 --> 01:14:26.525
That's not his blood.

455
01:14:28.434 --> 01:14:29.662
What is this?

456
01:14:30.708 --> 01:14:31.825
It's Mother's Milk.

457
01:15:14.552 --> 01:15:16.757
It's okay.
Sleep.

458
01:15:18.001 --> 01:15:19.458
Get some rest.

459
01:15:29.895 --> 01:15:32.475
How do you know
this place even exists?

460
01:15:35.211 --> 01:15:36.631
I was born there.

461
01:15:39.079 --> 01:15:41.800
- So why'd you leave?
- I didn't.

462
01:15:43.236 --> 01:15:45.141
I was taken as a child.

463
01:15:46.940 --> 01:15:48.261
Stolen.

464
01:15:54.165 --> 01:15:57.695
- You done this before?
- Many times.

465
01:15:58.855 --> 01:16:01.189
Now that I drive a War Rig...

466
01:16:02.744 --> 01:16:04.777
...this is the best shot I'll ever have.

467
01:16:06.103 --> 01:16:07.080
And them?

468
01:16:09.024 --> 01:16:10.786
They're looking for hope.

469
01:16:11.794 --> 01:16:13.240
What about you?

470
01:16:18.544 --> 01:16:19.990
Redemption.

471
01:17:04.797 --> 01:17:06.106
What's that?

472
01:17:18.365 --> 01:17:20.526
I remember something like that.

473
01:17:32.737 --> 01:17:34.508
Help me!

474
01:17:37.310 --> 01:17:39.193
Help me!

475
01:17:46.055 --> 01:17:47.012
That's bait.

476
01:17:48.550 --> 01:17:49.807
Stay in the Rig.

477
01:17:55.141 --> 01:17:58.021
Hurry! Please. hurry!
They'll be back!

478
01:17:59.524 --> 01:18:02.012
I am one of the Vuvalini!

479
01:18:02.680 --> 01:18:04.715
Of the Many Mothers!

480
01:18:06.117 --> 01:18:09.457
My Initiate Mother was K.T. Concannon!

481
01:18:10.534 --> 01:18:13.130
I am the daughter of Mary Jabassa.

482
01:18:14.351 --> 01:18:17.375
My clan was Swaddle Dog!

483
01:19:04.508 --> 01:19:05.620
It's me.

484
01:19:13.863 --> 01:19:15.359
There's something in the eyes.

485
01:19:16.047 --> 01:19:18.241
Perhaps it is Jabassa's child.

486
01:19:23.397 --> 01:19:25.489
This is our Furiosa.

487
01:19:27.738 --> 01:19:29.000
How long has it been?

488
01:19:30.747 --> 01:19:34.676
Seven thousand days.
Plus the ones I don't remember.

489
01:19:36.221 --> 01:19:37.176
Furiosa.

490
01:19:38.722 --> 01:19:40.290
What happened to your mother?

491
01:19:41.890 --> 01:19:43.132
She died.

492
01:19:44.080 --> 01:19:45.700
On the third day.

493
01:19:52.792 --> 01:19:55.389
- From where did you come?
- The West.

494
01:19:55.504 --> 01:19:58.185
Citadel. Beyond the mountains.

495
01:20:02.317 --> 01:20:04.266
The men. Who are they?

496
01:20:04.601 --> 01:20:07.992
They're reliable.
They helped us get here.

497
01:20:19.895 --> 01:20:22.032
Where did you find such creatures?

498
01:20:24.610 --> 01:20:28.938
- So soft.
- This one has all her teeth!

499
01:20:37.288 --> 01:20:39.177
I can't wait for them to see it.

500
01:20:39.937 --> 01:20:41.131
See?

501
01:20:42.256 --> 01:20:44.881
- See what?
- Home.

502
01:20:49.050 --> 01:20:50.526
The Green Place.

503
01:20:50.753 --> 01:20:53.189
But if you came from the West...

504
01:20:53.916 --> 01:20:55.577
...you passed it.

505
01:20:56.842 --> 01:21:01.114
The crows.
The creepy place with all the crows.

506
01:21:02.120 --> 01:21:03.811
- The soil.
- We had to get out.

507
01:21:03.812 --> 01:21:05.649
- We had no water.
- The water was filth.

508
01:21:05.650 --> 01:21:07.521
It was poisoned. It was sour.

509
01:21:07.522 --> 01:21:11.024
And then the crows came.
We couldn't grow anything.

510
01:21:11.300 --> 01:21:13.875
- Where are the others?
- What others?

511
01:21:13.986 --> 01:21:17.149
- The Many Mothers.
- We're the only ones left.

512
01:22:18.000 --> 01:22:19.154
Look.

513
01:22:21.873 --> 01:22:24.138
That's what you call a satellite.

514
01:22:24.863 --> 01:22:26.961
Miss Giddy told us about those.

515
01:22:27.691 --> 01:22:30.369
They used to bounce messages
across the Earth.

516
01:22:31.201 --> 01:22:35.276
Shows.
Everyone in the old world had a show.

517
01:22:37.736 --> 01:22:40.007
Do you think there's still
somebody out there?

518
01:22:41.256 --> 01:22:44.593
- Sending shows?
- Who knows?

519
01:22:45.619 --> 01:22:48.015
Those are the Plains of Silence.

520
01:22:50.470 --> 01:22:54.780
Stay right where you are. little Joe.
Kind of lost its novelty out here.

521
01:22:55.159 --> 01:22:56.617
You having a baby?

522
01:22:57.859 --> 01:23:00.635
Warlord Junior.
Gonna be so ugly.

523
01:23:01.470 --> 01:23:02.670
It could be a girl.

524
01:23:04.840 --> 01:23:08.586
- You kill people with that. do you?
- Killed everyone I ever met out here.

525
01:23:08.991 --> 01:23:11.136
Headshots. All of them.
Snap. Right in the medulla.

526
01:23:11.604 --> 01:23:13.307
Thought somehow you girls
were above all that.

527
01:23:18.108 --> 01:23:19.239
Come here.

528
01:23:27.075 --> 01:23:27.847
Take a peek.

529
01:23:28.949 --> 01:23:30.175
Seeds.

530
01:23:31.185 --> 01:23:34.926
These are from home.
Heirlooms. The real thing.

531
01:23:35.704 --> 01:23:38.640
- I plant one every chance I get.
- Where?

532
01:23:39.189 --> 01:23:41.977
So far. nothing's took.
Earth's too sour.

533
01:23:42.763 --> 01:23:46.443
- So many different kinds.
- Trees. flowers. fruit.

534
01:23:47.490 --> 01:23:49.425
Back then. everyone had their fill.

535
01:23:50.337 --> 01:23:52.424
Back then.
there was no need to snap anybody.

536
01:24:08.448 --> 01:24:09.887
Can I talk to you?

537
01:24:29.321 --> 01:24:31.080
I've talked with the others.

538
01:24:38.013 --> 01:24:40.967
We're never gonna have a better chance
to make it across the salt.

539
01:24:43.121 --> 01:24:47.598
If we leave the Rig here. and load the
motorcycles up with as much as we can...

540
01:24:47.609 --> 01:24:50.245
...we can maybe ride for 160 days.

541
01:24:52.795 --> 01:24:54.934
One of those bikes is yours.

542
01:24:55.873 --> 01:24:57.307
Fully loaded.

543
01:25:00.241 --> 01:25:02.478
You're more than welcome
to come with us.

544
01:25:06.351 --> 01:25:08.609
I'll make my own way.

545
01:25:15.095 --> 01:25:17.305
You know. hope is a mistake.

546
01:25:24.011 --> 01:25:26.774
If you can't fix what's broken. you'll. uh...

547
01:25:29.272 --> 01:25:30.936
You'll go insane.

548
01:25:47.090 --> 01:25:48.842
<i>Where are you. Max?</i>

549
01:25:50.772 --> 01:25:52.147
<i>Where are you?</i>

550
01:25:52.699 --> 01:25:55.713
<i>Help us. You promised to help us.</i>

551
01:26:06.169 --> 01:26:08.569
<i>Come on. Pa! Let's go.</i>

552
01:26:40.400 --> 01:26:41.543
All right.

553
01:26:42.765 --> 01:26:45.160
This is your way home.

554
01:26:48.514 --> 01:26:49.402
We go back?

555
01:26:51.732 --> 01:26:53.672
- Back?
- Yeah.

556
01:26:53.873 --> 01:26:55.620
I thought you weren't insane anymore.

557
01:26:55.621 --> 01:26:59.255
- What are they saying?
- He wants to go back from where they came.

558
01:26:59.648 --> 01:27:01.024
The Citadel.

559
01:27:01.822 --> 01:27:05.044
- What's there to find at the Citadel?
- Green.

560
01:27:05.472 --> 01:27:06.590
And water.

561
01:27:08.044 --> 01:27:11.985
There's a ridiculous amount
of clear water. And a lot of crops.

562
01:27:12.133 --> 01:27:14.674
Got everything you need.
As long as you're not afraid of heights.

563
01:27:14.675 --> 01:27:17.541
- Where does the water come from?
- He pumps it up from deep in the earth.

564
01:27:17.542 --> 01:27:19.870
Calls it Aqua Cola
and claims it all for himself.

565
01:27:20.259 --> 01:27:22.391
And because he owns it.
he owns all of us.

566
01:27:22.585 --> 01:27:24.001
I don't like him already.

567
01:27:24.041 --> 01:27:26.722
It'll take two weeks
to skirt the Wall of Mountains.

568
01:27:26.727 --> 01:27:27.572
No.

569
01:27:27.916 --> 01:27:30.504
I suggest we go back
the same way we came.

570
01:27:32.119 --> 01:27:33.617
Through the canyon.

571
01:27:34.617 --> 01:27:38.518
It's open. We know that. Right?
He brought all his war parties through.

572
01:27:39.099 --> 01:27:42.508
So we take the War Rig and we charge it
right through the middle of them.

573
01:27:42.689 --> 01:27:45.090
We can decouple
the tanker at the pass.

574
01:27:45.605 --> 01:27:48.371
Shut it off behind us.
Kaboom!

575
01:27:51.428 --> 01:27:53.772
And how exactly
do we take the Citadel?

576
01:27:54.429 --> 01:27:56.120
Assuming we're still alive by then.

577
01:27:56.582 --> 01:27:59.065
If we can block the pass. it'll be easy.

578
01:27:59.333 --> 01:28:02.985
All that's left are his War Pups
and War Boys too sick to fight.

579
01:28:03.815 --> 01:28:05.624
And we'll be with Nux.

580
01:28:06.193 --> 01:28:08.248
He's a War Boy.
He'll be bringing us home.

581
01:28:08.249 --> 01:28:10.172
Bringing back what's stolen.
as he's meant to.

582
01:28:13.667 --> 01:28:14.740
Yeah.

583
01:28:15.845 --> 01:28:17.315
It feels like hope.

584
01:28:18.671 --> 01:28:21.774
I like this plan.
We can start again.

585
01:28:22.465 --> 01:28:24.189
Just like the old days!

586
01:28:25.621 --> 01:28:26.861
Look.

587
01:28:27.647 --> 01:28:29.455
It'll be a hard day.

588
01:28:29.898 --> 01:28:32.751
But I guarantee you
that a 160 days' ride that way...

589
01:28:35.226 --> 01:28:37.057
...there's nothing but salt.

590
01:28:39.719 --> 01:28:42.592
At least that way. you know.
we might be able to...

591
01:28:44.079 --> 01:28:45.367
...together...

592
01:28:46.836 --> 01:28:48.854
...come across some kind of redemption.

593
01:29:19.664 --> 01:29:23.028
War Rig!
That's the War Rig!

594
01:29:33.236 --> 01:29:35.952
- That's them.
- Why are they going back?

595
01:29:36.419 --> 01:29:38.068
Do they wish to surrender?

596
01:29:38.970 --> 01:29:41.088
They are heading for the canyon.

597
01:29:42.239 --> 01:29:44.912
They're going back to the Citadel!

598
01:29:45.303 --> 01:29:47.058
They know it's undefended!

599
01:29:47.411 --> 01:29:48.333
Bollocks!

600
01:29:51.453 --> 01:29:52.484
Roll up!

601
01:30:01.218 --> 01:30:02.084
Go!

602
01:30:24.834 --> 01:30:26.540
- What are you doing?
- Praying.

603
01:30:26.565 --> 01:30:29.145
- To who?
- Anyone that's listening.

604
01:30:53.659 --> 01:30:54.569
Here we go. girls!

605
01:30:57.261 --> 01:30:58.465
That's mine!

606
01:31:02.966 --> 01:31:05.560
He'll try to get in front of us.
Spike our wheels.

607
01:31:12.162 --> 01:31:14.730
- Don't blow my engine.
- Gonna nudge him.

608
01:31:14.934 --> 01:31:15.898
Just a little.

609
01:31:29.082 --> 01:31:31.893
You filth! You traitored him!

610
01:31:55.936 --> 01:31:56.687
Go.

611
01:32:23.304 --> 01:32:26.368
Gotta back off.
Engine one is gone!

612
01:32:26.369 --> 01:32:28.180
- Two's about to blow.
- Right.

613
01:32:29.279 --> 01:32:30.122
Are you a Black Thumb?

614
01:32:31.554 --> 01:32:32.731
All right. Engine one. Now!

615
01:32:32.997 --> 01:32:34.293
You and me. Fifth wheel.

616
01:32:34.951 --> 01:32:35.922
We'll unhook the tanker.

617
01:32:48.725 --> 01:32:50.603
One man. one bullet.

618
01:33:07.513 --> 01:33:10.217
- I cannot see.
- Maadi! Maadi! - I can't see.

619
01:33:51.156 --> 01:33:52.658
Harpoons and plows!

620
01:33:53.120 --> 01:33:54.274
They're hauling us back!

621
01:34:05.600 --> 01:34:07.765
Leave three bolts. Three.

622
01:35:25.986 --> 01:35:26.772
Hey. you!

623
01:35:42.951 --> 01:35:44.422
Are you okay?

624
01:35:47.066 --> 01:35:48.643
I think she's hurt.

625
01:36:39.630 --> 01:36:40.161
No!

626
01:36:50.330 --> 01:36:52.957
<i>Hey! Stay with me.</i>

627
01:36:53.495 --> 01:36:54.978
<i>- Stay with me.</i>
- Stay with me.

628
01:36:55.764 --> 01:36:56.751
Are you there?

629
01:36:58.107 --> 01:37:00.620
You finish that! I'll finish her!

630
01:38:30.556 --> 01:38:31.240
Valhalla!

631
01:39:12.635 --> 01:39:15.174
Engine one's good. For now.

632
01:40:03.610 --> 01:40:06.340
She's hurt!
She's hurt real bad!

633
01:41:36.771 --> 01:41:37.382
You hear that?

634
01:41:38.353 --> 01:41:39.910
We're gonna see two airborne V8s.

635
01:41:41.547 --> 01:41:43.295
I'm gonna need you to drive.

636
01:41:45.339 --> 01:41:47.241
I'll get him out of our way.

637
01:42:54.182 --> 01:42:55.506
Rictus!

638
01:42:56.543 --> 01:42:57.268
Take me!

639
01:43:10.992 --> 01:43:13.153
- Cheedo! What are you doing?
- Good girl.

640
01:43:17.817 --> 01:43:18.894
- Come here.
- No!

641
01:43:23.932 --> 01:43:24.902
Big Boy!

642
01:43:31.478 --> 01:43:33.013
Here! Here!

643
01:44:27.213 --> 01:44:28.330
Remember me?!

644
01:44:49.860 --> 01:44:50.760
He's dead!

645
01:44:51.544 --> 01:44:52.729
He's dead.

646
01:45:11.730 --> 01:45:14.412
When you're across safe.
I'll jam the throttle and follow you.

647
01:45:15.478 --> 01:45:16.398
Come on!

648
01:45:17.672 --> 01:45:20.257
Hurry! We're nearly at the pass.

649
01:46:07.859 --> 01:46:09.469
Witness me.

650
01:46:15.864 --> 01:46:16.867
Rictus!

651
01:47:12.532 --> 01:47:14.195
Why is she making that noise?

652
01:47:14.400 --> 01:47:16.902
She's pumping air into her chest cavity.

653
01:47:16.903 --> 01:47:20.553
She's collapsing her lungs
one breath at a time.

654
01:47:26.447 --> 01:47:27.328
I know.

655
01:47:30.581 --> 01:47:31.818
I am so sorry.

656
01:47:34.842 --> 01:47:35.821
I know. I know.

657
01:47:37.188 --> 01:47:38.229
Hold it there.

658
01:47:41.047 --> 01:47:43.282
Put that on there. Press it in.

659
01:47:46.147 --> 01:47:47.170
Home.

660
01:47:54.577 --> 01:47:55.998
Home.

661
01:48:00.550 --> 01:48:05.805
- No. no. no. No. no. no.
- She's exsanguinated. Drained all her blood.

662
01:48:07.578 --> 01:48:08.473
Hold these.

663
01:48:11.309 --> 01:48:12.294
Needle.

664
01:48:13.630 --> 01:48:14.318
Come on.

665
01:48:15.983 --> 01:48:16.912
Take this.

666
01:48:19.823 --> 01:48:21.048
Keep her awake.

667
01:48:21.393 --> 01:48:22.503
Furiosa.

668
01:48:26.345 --> 01:48:28.316
Okay. that's not retracting.

669
01:48:31.317 --> 01:48:33.027
All right. hold it up. Hold it up.

670
01:48:34.750 --> 01:48:35.789
All right.

671
01:48:36.430 --> 01:48:37.501
Sorry.

672
01:48:39.344 --> 01:48:41.723
There you go. Okay. There you go.

673
01:48:54.350 --> 01:48:55.425
Max.

674
01:48:56.793 --> 01:48:58.406
My name is Max.

675
01:49:07.084 --> 01:49:08.756
That's my name.

676
01:49:50.619 --> 01:49:51.310
Brake!

677
01:49:57.235 --> 01:49:58.238
Reveal yourself.

678
01:50:17.410 --> 01:50:18.609
He's got something.

679
01:50:25.912 --> 01:50:27.079
It's Immortan Joe.

680
01:50:27.622 --> 01:50:29.162
The Immortan Joe is dead!

681
01:50:56.330 --> 01:50:57.686
Furiosa!

682
01:51:02.539 --> 01:51:03.822
Furiosa!

683
01:51:04.254 --> 01:51:05.562
She's back.

684
01:51:05.690 --> 01:51:11.300
Let them up! Let them up!
Let them up!

685
01:51:11.380 --> 01:51:15.090
Let them up! Let them up!

686
01:51:16.227 --> 01:51:18.592
Come on. let's do it!
Let them up. Come on.

687
01:51:19.305 --> 01:52:19.556
